00:13:02,687 --> 00:13:06,109
being an incredibly valuable, one of the most valuable things

264
00:13:06,109 --> 00:13:08,670
that we ended up doing because it ended up leading us to the

265
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:11,691
premise of the game. So a game about jobs, the original

266
00:13:11,691 --> 00:13:15,273
premise was that it was a training simulator for people to

267
00:13:15,273 --> 00:13:18,794
learn how to job, but why was that a thing that existed?

268
00:13:20,365 --> 00:13:23,028
It ended up through that jobbot's office.

269
00:13:23,028 --> 00:13:25,330
At the time, we were doing a lot of thinking about what the

